article.headline: Alcorn State 78, Miss. Valley St. 61
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Point guard Alleo Frazier scored a career-high 19 points and Alcorn State beat Mississippi Valley State 78-61 on Saturday night. Delvin Thompson and Juan Wyatt had 17 points apiece, Clif Douglass finished with 14 points, Frazier was 7-of-8 from the field and the Braves shot a season-best 57.7 percent in the victory. Kadrian Bryant led the Delta Devils with 21 points and 12 rebounds, and Carl Lucas added 10 points. Alcorn State (6-16, 6-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference) led 41-26 at halftime after an 8-0 run and held on for its second straight win since halting its two-game losing streak at Grambling State on Monday. Mississippi Valley State (6-15, 6-6) lost its fifth straight since a four-game winning streak was snapped two weeks ago by Jackson State. The Delta Devils were just 3-of-17 from 3-point range. Mississippi Valley State won the first meeting 67-59 on Jan. 14.
